creatine creatine is one of the most vastly researched supplement and ha been promoted in the fitness industry in the last few year  according to research  supplementation with creatine monohydrate ha been shown to increase skeletal muscle mass  lean body mass and muscle fibre size  research also suggests past this and it may encourage healthy aging and benefit brain health  do i need creatine  creatine supplementation can be hugely beneficial for athletic performance and study have also showed it can have an impact on body composition  prolonged creatine ingestion inducing an increase in fat free mass   do i need to load creatine  nope  <Number> daily will suffice   the idea to saturate the muscle is just to experience benefit sooner   increase water consumption when you start taking creatine  when should i take it  evidence doe suggest post workout is superior to pre workout  are there any side effect   bloating  this is due to the muscle absorbing the water with the creatine  very common and usually subsides when the muscle are saturated   stomach discomfort  may cause stomach sensitivity like bloating  #creatine #supplement #nutritioncoach #realnutrition #realresults #fitness #fitliving #strengthtraining

caption: never underestimate stress ü§Ø   did you know    stress is not just feeling stressed   i always ask my client about stress level  most people respond with either yes im stressed or no im not stressed   stress is a lot more complex than feeling stressed     stress can present itself from so many thing  some which im sure youre aware of  some which you wont realise üôà  the above is just a handful    when youre stressed body switch on fight or flight mode  release adrenaline  nora adrenaline    üéØadrenaline increase heart rate  breath faster and tense muscle  üéØnoradrenaline diverts blood from  unessential area during fight or flight  reproductive system  digestive and skin  üéØcortisol raise blood pressure and blood sugar   we need stress hormone in our body  but the problem arises when they are   implication of increased stress hormone ‚úîsuppress other hormone  sex ‚úîsuppressing immune system  libido ‚úîincreased blood pressure ‚úîhaving impact on digestion ‚úîincreasing acne and obesity risk  what can you do  ‚≠ê reduce controllable stress ‚≠ê take so me time every day ‚≠ê meditate ‚≠ê rest and relax more ‚≠ê talk to people more  about issue etc  ‚≠ê seek medical attention if necessary   #howstressedareyou

caption: comparison is the thief of joy ü§¶‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è   i see this one a lot    you are individual  you are not like anyone else  so why would you compare yourself to anyone else  ü§∑‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è   most of the time the circumstance arent even comparable  let give you some example ‚ùé comparing your image to celebrity ‚ùé comparing your performance to athlete ‚ùé comparing your body to fitness influencers   if you are not where you want to be  being honest it is probably something you are or are not doing  but you are making life a hell of a lot more difficult for yourself by setting unrealistic goal and target üéØ   ‚úî start by setting some realistic goal ‚úî progression over perfection ‚úî be consistent  stop giving it a short term tag  look at the long term  look at your future self  ‚úî find something you enjoy  you are more likely to stick to it   stop blaming other people and start looking at what you need to do to get where you want to be üëä and remember no number on the scale will make you happy unless you deal with the shit in your head üß†

caption: training and nutrition aesthetic v performance   some of the difference include  <Number>  calorie requirement may be different  performance goal usually require maintenance calorie or even a surplus depending on how active you are  aesthetic goal usually require being in a calorie deficit    <Number>  training look different  training for aesthetic is usually some bodybuilding format with some form of light cardio  training for performance is usually sport specific like pitch training  strength session or even high volume session like crossfit    <Number>  nutrient profile may be different  firstly  weight loss requires you to be in a calorific deficit  technically  you could eat <Number> mar bar a day and lose weight  i wouldnt recommend it  but youd achieve your goal  where a if you tried to perform at your best for a sport on <Number> mar bar a day  i can not imagine youd be performing very well  nutrition for aesthetic can be a simple a calorie in versus calorie out  nutrition for performance is much more intricate  do you have enough fuel  are you recovering ok  do you have a full nutrient profile  are you consuming good fat for hormonal balance and recovery    these are some of the main difference in nutrition and training when you have different goal  can you think of more  ü§î üì∏ <Handle>

capability and pregnancy are different so go with how youre feeling  dont over exert yourself  and talk with your coach and doctor üôè   nutrition  this idea of eating double for two is non sense üôà  calorie shouldnt even be increased in first trimester  daily calorie should be increased by about <Number> in <Number> trimester and <Number> in <Number> trimester   there may be food aversion üí•üí•üí•fun fact üí•üí•üí•   i didnt eat fruit or vegetable until i went to college  studying to be a nutritionistüôà   and at that it wa very limited  maybe the odd orange and carrot with dinner  üôà <Handle> wa my saviour when i moved to sheffield with her  she had me eating food i would never ever eat üòÇeven if i did make her chop vegetable into the tiniest piece üòÇ my point is i changed a habit  not only did i change it  i absolutely did a <Number> ü§ó  i dont do thing by half üòù    when people come to me with  i dont eat this or i dont like that or i dont eat any vegetable etc  i see that a a choice  it absolutely fine if you are one of these people and choose to be picky   no one is expected to like everything üòÇ i still can not eat cauliflower and im not a fan of asparagus but i am much more open to trying new thing  and not once  because that is not enough  they say if you still can not stand something after the <Number> try  there a good chance you like it  ü§∑‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è   üí•üí•üí•another fun fact üí•üí•üí• i only started eating salad about <Number> year ago  after year of telling myself i dont like iceberg lettuce and tomato  still dont  i realised thats not the only salad that exists üòëüò≥ if you think you dont like salad  dont make it with item you dont like üòÖüòú i base most of mine on rocket or spinach  add a much colour usually beetroot  carrot  cucumber  sun dried tomato  a cheese and finish it with fruit üòç i love fruit in salad  and salad shouldnt just be a summer thingüö´üö´üö´add a warm meat  fish or meat alternative  add a warm grain like cous cous  quinoa or pasta and voila ‚òëÔ∏è‚òëÔ∏è‚òëÔ∏è   stop holding yourself back from the healthiest version of you ü§ó #fitfood #nutriton #nutritionist #fitlifestyle #fitliving #fitfam #fitaustralia #irishfitfam

what defines health  ü§î   let me tell you what i think it is    ‚ùåhealth is not a low body fat ‚ùåhealth is not training excessively ‚ùåhealth is not clean eating ‚ùåhealth is not being mindful ‚ùåhealth is not sleeping <Number> hour a day ‚ùåhealth is not <Number> thing   health is different to everyone  health ha a physical aspect but it ha a huge mental aspect too  obsessing about calorie is not healthy  yoloing isnt either  a measure on a scale is certainly not a definition of health  eating whole nutritious food is amazing but if you are constantly thinking about all the food you cant have   thats not healthy  sleeping <Number> hour a day but stressing for the other <Number> is not healthy  and training is important but if it consuming you  affecting relationship  affecting your physical or mental health that obviously is not healthy    i want to help people  i want to help them develop a healthy relationship with food and exercise  i want to help them stop being so hard on themselves and celebrate little victory  i want to cut this idea that exercise is just a way to burn calorie  i want people to stop obsessing over calorie  i want to help ‚ù§Ô∏è if you want my help  pm me  #happiness #goodrelationships #healthyrelationships #behappy #behealthy #fitlifestyle #fitliving #fitaustralia

caption: a you can see from my feed i have began to love crossfit üíã   i didnt always love it and actually i wa a huge skeptic  my friend know this a some of them have questioned me on it ü§î but my view and opinion on so many thing over the year have changed  i also believed that a restrictive clean  diet wa the healthiest diet there could be  forgetting the impact that restriction ha on your mental health ü§∑‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏èü§∑‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è   i have made so many mistake over the year ive been in the health and fitness industry  ive called food good  and bad   and ive shunned certain exercise routine  but from experience come knowledge and wisdom  üôè and i am a lot more open minded to thing now üëå   i dont think crossfit is for everyone  it a seriously stringent training regime which requires a huge level of mobility  strength and conditioning  even at a regressed level  it can be overwhelming and injury level can be high due to poor training technique or poor coaching  this is obviously not all coach   but i also dont think everyone should be running  poor running technique can contribute to any number of problem with joint  ligament  tendon or muscle strain    i am a firm believer in anyone starting out on a fitness journey  to look around  find what work for you  there not a one size fit all  i would normally say to get a coach to steer you in the right direction and then youll find a lifestyle you can enjoy ‚ù§Ô∏è because exercise should not be a punishment üôè #fitliving #ineedtopostthiscauseiwontbetrainingforawhile #fitlifestyle #fitlife #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #fitfam #irishfitfam

what is iron and why is it important    iron is an essential mineral needed by the body  it primary function is to transport oxygen in the haemoglobin of red blood cell so the cell can produce energy  it also help to remove carbon   how much iron do you need and where do we get it    infant and toddler need more iron than adult because their body are still growing  woman need more iron than men due to menstruation  woman require about  while men need just   iron is found in food like  shellfish  liver  red meat  spinach  kale and fortified cereal  haem iron is the iron we get from animal source and is most easily absorbed in the body  non haem iron come from plant source and is not a easily absorbed so may require supplementation in vegetarian and vegan  vitamin c is also essential for iron absorption  it ‚Äô s found in many fruit like blackcurrants  strawberry  kiwi and orange  adding orange juice or fruit to an iron rich meal can help absorption    how do i know if i ‚Äô m deficient in iron    common symptom of iron deficiency anaemia include  fatigue  paleness  difficulty exercising  or have a fast heartbeat  it is important to never self diagnose  too much iron is toxic and should not be taken unless recommended by a medical professional    female athlete are at risk of iron deficiency anaemia due to menstruation and high exercise output  make sure if you are showing any of the symptom to get it checked out by a doctor and never self diagnose  #irondeficiency #anaemia #healthylifestyle #healthyliving #athlete #fitliving #fitlife #fitlifestyle #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption: one of the most common question i get asked is about a pre match meal  well let me tell you  pre match fuel begin long before the pre match meal  üòÉ   a discussed in previous post  carbohydrate are the main fuel source involved in gaa  we can store <Number> <Number> in our liver and <Number> <Number> in our muscle a glycogen  but a glucose is constantly being used a a fuel source it is constantly depleting therefore we need to top it up regularly    pre match nutriton begin the day before a game  so if you play sunday at <Number>  you should be topping glycogen store from <Number> saturday  i recommend a carbohydrate source with each meal like cous cous for lunch  potato for dinner and oat for breakfast the following morning  closer to game time  fruit is a great source of caÃÅrbohydrate  protein is also essential  a athlete we are constantly in recovery mode for our next session so protein need to be a part of our pre match routine  although it wont be used a fuel it is an important element for muscle repair etc    some donts the day of a game ‚ùå‚ùå‚ùå ‚ùé high fat food are harder to break down in the body and may cause gastrointestinal upset so best to avoid large quantity of fat  save them for afterwards when we need to reduce inflammation ‚ùé high fibre food can also cause gastrointestinal issue and while fibre is a vital part of a healthy diet  it best to avoid large quantity before game ‚ùé strong flavoured food   some do ‚úîÔ∏è‚úîÔ∏è‚úîÔ∏è ‚òëÔ∏è nutrient dense food with a caÃÅrbohydrate and protein element üëâoats with whey protein  egg and toast  fruit salad with greek yogurt  chicken and pasta  fish and potato ‚òëÔ∏è dont forget about water  hydration is a key pre match ritual hope this help üòÉ never change a routine the day of a game  slowly make change in the day leading up to a game üëå #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #fitlife #prematch #nutrition #fitliving #fitfam #irishfitfam

listen up  this one is an important üëÇ   yes macro are important  carbohydrate is the main source of energy for most sport  protein is essential for repair and recovery  fat are anti inflammatory and necessary for fat soluble vitamin transport  yes your macronutrients which convert into energy are fuel for the body    but what about micronutrient  phytonutrients and zoo chemical  these dont directly fuel u but they are also vital to the functioning of the human body  they are responsible for vital internal function and without them our body would not be able to asorb nutrient or convert them to energy  they are vital for gut health  immunity  nervous system functioning  nutrient absorbtion  digestion  the list go on  üìÉ a human  our body dont just do one thing at a time  even if we think we are   just to be alive  all our system are working internally  imagine adding eating and drinking to that  now let add a job  let add a family  let add exercise  our body are constantly working  there is no off switch üì¥ sometimes are body are under serious strain  if we are not getting the vital nutrient we need to keep up with this pressure  major problem can occur within the body  üòû   i dont give opinion on this very often but im going to for this one  if you are constantly  macro and not focusing on food quality thats fine  youll get the fuel you need for your body  but overall  internally  you are not focusing on the other function in your body  your body is more than just an engine that you need to fuel  it complex and deserves to be treated like your most important possession  because really  thats what it is ü§îü§îü§î #foodisnorethanfuel #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #fitlife #fitlifestyle #fitliving #healthylifestyle #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption: if youre like me and calorie counting is not your thing  all is not lost  yes calorie matter but so doe your life and if you absolutely hate the thought of entering everything you eat into my fitness pal  a a trainer i would never force you üòâmost if not all of my client have achieved their incredible result from never having entered a calorie or macro into myfitnesspal üëèüëèüëè   i am not slating it  it obviously work for people  and whoever us it and enjoys tracking  go you üëç there are some reason why the calorie on our food label dont actually correlate to real life though üôàso it not a <Number>  fool proof method  üëâ fibre and resistant starch are often overestimated üëâ some of the data is outdated or the analysis of it wa imprecises üëâ only one product is tested so it doesnt take into account product variety üëâ soil composition and animal diet are not taken into account üëâ ripeness at time of harvest  ever taste in season irish strawberry v imported out of seasonüòè üëâ storage  preparation and cooking of food can change nutritional composition of food   some of my top tip if youre not interested in tracking  üí• protein at each meal  approx <Number> per kg bw  üí• load up on veggie  full of micros and volume  low in calorie  üí• portion size  use a smaller plate and watch those caÃÅrb and fat portion  üí• fibre rich food  fruit  veggie  legume  some complex carbs  üí• drink plenty of water  a lot of the time were actually thirsty not hungry   and just keep active  technically  you dont have to if youre nutrition is on point  but come on  we are so lucky to be able to exercise  enjoy it üòç #fitlife #fitlifestyle #fitliving #balance #balancedlifestyle #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #fitfam #irishfitfam

season a you do during championship    think about it though  preseason is usually gym based with maybe one pitch session so activity level are not a high  compare that to full on championship mode  you may be on the pitch <Number> time a week with one gym session  and this only take one sport into consideration  you may have multiple sport  if activity level increase so too should calorie and vice versa  if we are in a period of lowered activity  calorie should therefore be lower  overall calorie are determined by gender  weight  activity level and goal    macronutrient requirement will also be different  protein requirement will be high in both case a the need for recovery will be high  post gym session or post match both require high protein  protein target are usually  per kg bw    fat are also important for recovery and to reduce inflammation  these should be approximately <Number>  of our overall calorie intake    carbohydrate is our main energy source during sport  pre season however  requires le carbohydrate intake  we are focused on more short burst of energy like gym work or sprint which use a different energy system to match  we don ‚Äô t need to consume carbohydrate with every meal during pre season and while our calorie requirement are also lower here might be a good place to start  we could substitute our complex carbohydrate rice with a lower calorie cauliflower rice or breakfast could focus more on a larger omelette with extra veggie rather than <Number> slice of bread  these are just option of how to reduce calorie but keep bulk and not caption: let talk stress üôà the whole world is taking about calorie deficit and training hard  did you know that maybe youre grinding  too much ü§î   what do i mean  üëâ were always told  be in a calorie deficit to lose weight and exercise more  right  but what if youre body is under chronic stress and you are not sleeping right  will this affect you  yes    chronic and acute stress release hormone and neuro transmitter that tell our body to go into fight or flight  mode  these hormone and neurotransmitter especially norepinephrine switch off digestion and the gi tract making it very difficult to absorb nutrient üö´üö´üö´   my own experience with stress  and how i learned to copeü§îü§îü§î i have been a worry wart from day dot  and a control freak  i used to stress out so badly  i remember the tell tale sign would be on my skin if i wa going through a really bad period of stress üò© during my leaving cert i lost load of weight and my hair started falling out due to stress üòîbefore my dad died  he asked me to try and relax and something triggered in me  i knew i needed to put thing in place or i would end up running myself into the ground  and i had improved so much until this yearüôÑ this year tested me  a roller coaster doesnt do it justice  so i realised i needed help  i started seeing a counsellor and i have been seeing her for the past month üòä  my issue are not a simple a im stressed they go way back so thats what i needed help with     what can you do  so while you may not need to go to the extreme i did  you need to manage your stress level  the body doe not want to be in fight or flight mode  it want to be in rest and digest  mode  so you need to sort your stress out acute or chronic üö´üö´   self care is vitally important  i have only really started learning that since my dad died  this year with the help of my counsellor ive realised that who going to look after me if im trying to look after everyone elseü§î it absolutely
